    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-03T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-03T01:00:00-05:00" n="208"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3901: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1"
                            type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-03T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 3, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 3—6:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Japanese Consulate General states that at 5:30 a.m. today when three Japanese
                    destroyers [were?] passing Woosung forts on the way to Sasebo they were fired
                    upon by forts. Fire was returned. Japanese Consulate General states Japanese
                    arranging to occupy Woosung forts.</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Legation and Nanking for information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CES1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
